    <h2>FAQ</h2>
    <h3>Is Perplexity better than ChatGPT for research?</h3>
    <p>Yes. Perplexity is purpose-built for search with real-time citations. ChatGPT's browsing is good but less reliable for source verification.</p>
    <h3>Can Perplexity replace Google Search?</h3>
    <p>For many knowledge workers, yes. Perplexity summarizes multiple sources instantly with citations, saving time vs. opening 10 blue links.</p>
    <h3>Does ChatGPT have citations like Perplexity?</h3>
    <p>Sometimes, but not consistently. ChatGPT's browsing mode may provide sources, but it often paraphrases without attribution.</p>
    <h3>Can I use Perplexity and ChatGPT together?</h3>
    <p>Absolutely. Use Perplexity to research and gather sources, then use ChatGPT to draft, rewrite, and expand on the findings.</p>
